Libevent
Libevent



 &reftitle.intro;


  Libevent is a library that provides a mechanism to execute a callback
  function when a specific event occurs on a file descriptor or after a
  timeout has been reached.



  More information about Libevent can be found at &url.libevent;.



   The libevent extension is unmaintained; consider to use the
   event extension instead.





